---
import ContentPaginated from '~/components/common/ContentPaginated.astro';
import PageLayout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';

import Posts from '~/components/blocks/Posts.astro';
import Projects from '~/components/blocks/Projects.astro';
import Ad from '~/components/structures/Ad.astro';
import NeedConsultationCard from '~/components/structures/NeedConsultationCard.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'The Official Business Pathfinder Site | Chronicles from the Trenches.',
  description:
    'The Official Site of "The Business Pathfinder Chronicles." Access 28 years of trench-earned expertise: Crisis case studies, navigating corporate storms, high-stakes international deals, and radical business survival strategies for the new economic reality.',
  ignoreTitleTemplate: true,
};
const breadCrumbLinks = [{ text: 'Home', href: '/' }];

// Load posts
import { findLatestPosts } from '~/utils/blog';
const posts = await findLatestPosts({ count: 2 });

// Load projects
import { findLatestProjects } from '~/utils/project';
const projects = await findLatestProjects({ count: 2 });
---

<PageLayout
  {breadCrumbLinks}
  {metadata}
  heroItems={[
    {
      title: 'The Architecture of Success',
      description:
        'A strategic leader anticipates the inevitable, preventing the competition from executing their plans.',
      bgImage: '~/assets/images/hero-1.webp',
    },
    {
      title: 'Concentration of Force',
      description:
        'Fragmented efforts lead to a mirage of victory. True mastery is merging disparate streams into one unified, irresistible current.',
      bgImage: '~/assets/images/hero-2.webp',
    },
    {
      title: 'The Philosophy of Victory',
      description:
        'You win on the battlefield, not in the classroom. Expertise is the wisdom to capitalize on—even your own—mistakes.',
      bgImage: '~/assets/images/hero-3.webp',
    },
  ]}
>
  <ContentPaginated>
    <h1>The Business Pathfinder Chronicles.</h1>
    <h2>Real-Life Business Strategy: Convert Intuition into Measurable KPIs.</h2>
    <p>
      Big business has its shiny, polished facade—and then it has the real backstage. That's the place that smells less
      like expensive cologne and more like sour milk, burnt coffee, and the smoke from epic mistakes that went up in
      flames.
    </p>
    <p>
      This backstage is where game-changing decisions are made, where passions run high, and where textbook-defying
      stories are born.
    </p>
    <p>Welcome to my site, The Business Pathfinder Chronicles.</p>
    <h2>Who is a Business Pathfinder?</h2>
    <p>
      What the heck is a Business Pathfinder? Why that name? What are we even talking about here? These are the first
      questions I get when people stumble upon my project.
    </p>
    <p>This term is my personal formula for the job—it’s the key to understanding my entire philosophy.</p>
    <p>
      This isn't consulting in the narrow, dry, snooze-fest sense of the word. In a world where consulting is broken
      down into a million specialized silos, I bring a full-cycle perspective.
    </p>
    <p>
      A Business Pathfinder is NOT "just another consultant". Think of me as a Synthesis Specialist who uses a
      magnifying glass to follow the tracks of problems and possibilities. I examine the company's entire organism—from
      its financial anatomy and legal nerve endings to its marketing bloodstream and cultural DNA.
    </p>
    <p>
      It’s the art of investigation. I’m like Sherlock Holmes, but for business, where there are no trivial details—only
      clues.
    </p>
    <h2>Credentials Earned in the Trenches</h2>
    <p>My 28-year professional journey is a map of real battles, not textbook drills.</p>
    <p>
      I’ve been on both sides of the fence: as a founder of a construction company landing government contracts and a
      stockbroker, as a turnaround specialist (who literally resurrected a sinking dairy plant), and as the architect of
      complex M&A deals.
    </p>
    <p>
      I’ve involuntarily ended up in the middle of corporate wars, managed to come out afloat with an equity stake,
      built sales systems from the ground up, and learned to hold my breath underwater in periods of crisis, when
      everyone else was scrambling for a life raft.
    </p>
    <p>You won't find names of people, companies, funds, or banks in these Chronicles. And it’s not about modesty.</p>
    <p>
      It’s about respect —respect for the NDAs I sign, for the people I’ve had the honor of working with, and for the
      rules of the big league game.
    </p>
    <p>
      Business is a closed club, and the highest currency you can trade in is discretion—the ability to keep a secret.
    </p>
    <p>I’m the one who gets handed the keys to the backstage, and I value that trust more than anything.</p>
    <h2>So, what are you going to find in The Business Pathfinder Chronicles?</h2>
    <p>
      You won't find dry, dusty MBA textbook cases here. These are raw, real-life stories from my practice—sometimes
      hilarious, sometimes dramatic, and sometimes downright unbelievable—where I’ve boiled off all the fluff and left
      you with just the essence.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        The time the entire commercial department of a major Trading House hated my guts because I made them finally
        play fair.
      </li>
      <li>
        The saga of surviving a corporate perfect storm while looking for an investor, and how I didn't just win but
        actually walked away with an equity stake.
      </li>
      <li>
        The transformation story: how the 2008 global meltdown forced me, a stockbroker, to reboot myself as an Internet
        marketer and find new opportunities in the rubble of old business models.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      I’m a firm believer that the most solid knowledge is earned on the battlefield, not in the classroom. It's about
      having the wisdom and humor to learn the right lessons even from your own screw-ups and bruises. I’m a
      practitioner who knows how to talk about the complex stuff in plain English.
    </p>
    <h2>Why You Should Be Reading The Business Pathfinder Chronicles</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>First off</strong>, this is free access to experience that I paid for with sweat and a whole lot of blood.
      I’m not sharing this for self-promotion; I’m doing it so you can spot your own mistakes in my missteps and find
      possible solutions. Watching the falls and the wins of others is the fastest shortcut to building your own
      priceless experience.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Second,</strong> if you’re here right now, it’s because you’re not looking for theories or motivational speeches—you’re
      looking for results:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        You’re an Investor who’s tired of dumping money into "leaky buckets" and is finally ready to see a real return.
      </li>
      <li>
        You’re an Entrepreneur who feels the business has hit an invisible ceiling and needs a fresh set of eyes because
        the P&L reports are telling an ugly truth.
      </li>
      <li>
        You’re a Startup Innovator with fire in your belly, who knows you need more than just faith—you need a
        bulletproof strategy and the right investments to make a breakthrough.
      </li>
      <li>
        Or maybe you're just a Person or Expert in your field who wants to forge a "Personal Brand" into a sustainable
        business model through real work, not by listening to the latest "Success-Peddler" selling you their "Secret
        Sauce" at a seminar.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>Your Personal Brand is, without a doubt, a bona fide business project in this day and age.</p>
    <p>
      I dare you to try: The Business Pathfinder Chronicles are a genuine page-turner. We cut the pretentious, boring
      jargon and replace it with self-deprecating humor, genuine wit, and—most importantly—deep respect for your
      intelligence.
    </p>
    <p>
      I use real examples to show you how to stop the chaos, restore order, convert intuition into measurable KPIs, and
      turn sheer panic into a crystal-clear action plan.
    </p>
    <p>
      In my stories, you might just recognize the echoes of your own toughest challenges—and find a reason to crack a
      smile.
    </p>
    <p>
      And who knows? Maybe we’ll write the next story about conquering the absurd together, when we sit down over a cup
      of coffee and discuss growth opportunities instead of just problems.
    </p>
    <div>
      <p>Sincerely Yours,</p>
      <p><strong>Business Pathfinder</strong></p>
    </div>
  </ContentPaginated>

  <Posts
    title="Insights"
    data={posts.map((post, index) => {
      return {
        id: post.id,
        imageSrc: post.image,
        href: post.permalink,
        label: 'Announcement',
        title: post.excerpt ?? post.title,
        direction: index % 2 ? 'left' : ('right' as 'left' | 'right'),
      };
    })}
  />
  <Projects
    title="My Projects"
    layout={{
      columns: 3,
      rows: 1,
      spans: [{ col: 2 }, { col: 1 }],
    }}
    data={projects.map((project) => {
      return {
        id: project.id,
        imageSrc: project.image,
        href: project.permalink,
        title: project.title,
        excerpt: project.excerpt ?? '',
      };
    })}
  />
  <Ad />
  <NeedConsultationCard class="md:hidden max-w-full" />
</PageLayout>
